  "text": "All radiographs were independently and blindly graded by clinical veterinarians [CITATION_1] ) and in all views were normal (score ¼ 0) prior to inoculation on day 0. Within the control group, all three animals were graded at 2 at 5 dpi with severe interstitial infiltrates seen early that progressed to pulmonary consolidation within the caudal and middle lung lobes on 7 dpi (score ¼ 3). Both the hyperimmune plasma treatment and the mAb treatment group on average had lower graded radiographs in comparison to the control group. On 7 dpi, one hyperimmune plasma-treated animal was characterized as having grade 1 (H2, mild interstitial pulmonary infiltrates in the left caudal lung lobes), while the remaining two hyperimmune plasma-treated animals had either moderate (H1, grade 2) or severe (H3, grade 3) radiographic signs. One mAb-treated animal had normal radiographic findings (M2, grade 0) throughout the duration of the study, whereas the other two animals (M1, M3) were scored as presenting with mild radiographic findings (grade 1) (Fig. 2B and C and Fig. S1 ).",
